  <compounddef id="KEYMAP" kind="page">
    <compoundname>KEYMAP</compoundname>
    <title>KEYMAP Keyword</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">KEYMAP<sp/>string-expression</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Loads a <bold>keyboard mapping</bold> by name from the <computeroutput>/system/keymaps</computeroutput> directory.</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>The value of <computeroutput>string-expression</computeroutput> should be the <bold>map name</bold> (for example <computeroutput>&quot;en-GB&quot;</computeroutput>). <linebreak/>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The interpreter will try to load <computeroutput>/system/keymaps/&lt;name&gt;.keymap</computeroutput>. <linebreak/>
 Example: <computeroutput>KEYMAP &quot;en-GB&quot;</computeroutput> â†’ <computeroutput>/system/keymaps/en-GB.keymap</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Paths are <bold>case-insensitive</bold>. <linebreak/>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>.</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>..</computeroutput> are <bold>not supported</bold> in paths.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Only the keymaps that actually exist under <computeroutput>/system/keymaps</computeroutput> can be loaded. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Do not assume a particular layout is available.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>If a keymap cannot be found or loaded, a runtime error is raised (catchable with </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para><ulink url="https://github.com/brainboxdotcc/retro-rocket/wiki/ONERROR"><computeroutput>ON ERROR</computeroutput></ulink>).</para>
</simplesect>
<hruler/>
</para>
<para><heading level="5">Example</heading>
</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Load<sp/>British<sp/>English<sp/>keyboard<sp/>layout<sp/>(if<sp/>installed)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">KEYMAP<sp/>&quot;en-GB&quot;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><heading level="5">Notes</heading>
</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>The setting affects how keyboard input is interpreted by the system. <linebreak/>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>To see which keymaps are present, inspect the <computeroutput>/system/keymaps</computeroutput> directory with your usual tools. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
